Cell["Introduction", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.530472405389732*^9, 3.530472409445242*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "In \"Percolation Experiments 1 & 2\" I attempted to address the question: \
How does mean internodal resistance respond when the number of resistors \
(edges) in a random n-node circuit (graph) is increased, from zero to the \
saturation value \[EmptyUpTriangle]= n(n-1)/2 ? Using the ",
 StyleBox["Klein-Randi\[CAcute]",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " method to compute internodal resistances for large samples of such random \
matrices, I was led to \"percolation curves\" of the following form:"
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.530472482859103*^9, 3.530472529845867*^9}, {
   3.5304725609491034`*^9, 3.5304727078272953`*^9}, {3.530472756624379*^9, 
   3.530472760687886*^9}, {3.5304728440548983`*^9, 3.5304728606612473`*^9}, 
   3.5304743378853903`*^9, {3.53047475701195*^9, 3.530474847027356*^9}}],

