Cell[TextData[{
 "Those three graphs are again permutationally equivalent, and again give \
unequal readings if we suppose that our ohmmeter is attached always to (say) \
nodes #1 and #2. Each is now a ",
 StyleBox["connected ",
  FontVariations->{"Underline"->True}],
 "graph, a graph to which the Klein - Randi\[CAcute] method now does pertain \
: its application in the latter instance leads to a result "
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.530724344027935*^9, 3.5307243494294443`*^9}, {
  3.530724489561922*^9, 3.5307245504913054`*^9}, {3.530724608134493*^9, 
