Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["\<\
Return to the percolation problem that first motivated this work\
\>", "Subsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.530763200764613*^9, 3.530763257927952*^9}}],

Cell[TextData[{
 "We must be clear about (1) ",
 StyleBox["what it is we propose to measure",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 " (resistance ",
 StyleBox["vs",
  FontSlant->"Italic"],
 ". conductance) and (2) ",
 StyleBox["how we propose to conduct those measurements",
  FontWeight->"Bold"],
 ". In all cases, we propose to drop m unit resistors onto an n-node graph, \
with m ranging from 1 to \[CapitalDelta][n].\n\nI illustrate the alternatives \
as they relate to the simplest possible non-trivial case n =  3 (m = 1, 2, \
3). I use \[FilledCircle] to indicate nodes, and ",
 StyleBox["\[FilledCircle]",
  FontColor->RGBColor[1, 0, 0]],
 " to indicate nodes to which the ohmmeter probes are connected."
}], "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.5308261616548233`*^9, 3.5308263034369287`*^9}, {
  3.53082633496807*^9, 3.530826341709876*^9}, {3.530826377523334*^9, 
  3.530826437169416*^9}, {3.530827472552681*^9, 3.530827622961204*^9}, {
  3.5308276553459682`*^9, 3.5308276988350573`*^9}, {3.530827765722843*^9, 
  3.530827769417244*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[""], "Input",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.530827735362507*^9, 3.530827737424*^9}}],

Cell[CellGroupData[{

Cell["Fixed probe protocol", "Subsubsection",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.530827789069525*^9, 3.53082780323431*^9}}],

Cell["\<\
Clip the meter probes to a selected pair of nodes. Drop a resistor randomly, \
many times.  \
\>", "Text",
 CellChangeTimes->{{3.530828309321747*^9, 3.530828363642169*^9}, {
  3.530828473276031*^9, 3.530828475919574*^9}}],

Cell[BoxData[
